condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A (1) (a) | Description :The Recipient shall maintain APIX, which shall be responsiblefor supervision of Project implementation, implementation of Parts A and D, and financial management and procurement activities |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A (1) (b) | Description :The Recipient shall maintain, within APIX, the DDTH ProgramUnit, the Works Unit, the Environmental and Social Unit and the DDTH Resettlement Unit | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A (3) | Description :The Recipient shall maintain AGETIP which shall be responsible forthe day-to-day implementation of Parts B.1 and C of the Project | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A (4) | Description :AGETIP and APIX shall sign the necessary Implementation Agreementsfor the implementation of AGETIP's part of the Project | Due Date :13-Oct-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A (4) | Description :AGETIP shall carry out the Project in accordance with theImplementation Agreements with APIX | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A (5) | Description :The Recipient shall carry out and ensure that the Concessionairecarries out the Project in accordance with the Concession Agreement and monitor and evaluate its progress | Frequency :Quarterly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, B (1) | Description :The Recipient shall enter into a subsidiary agreement with theProject Implementation Entity | Due Date :13-Oct-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, D | Description :The Recipient shall implement the project activities in accordance withBasic and Supplemental Social and Environment Safeguard Instruments and shall provide to the Association quarterly reports |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, B (3) | Description :The Recipient shall have its Financial Statements audited inaccordance with the provisions of Section 4.09(b) of the General Conditions | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, 3 | Description :The Recipient shall have paid all indisputed amounts outstanding to itscontractors for construction of the Phase 1 Highway Work and the Phase 2 Highway work | Due Date :30-Sep-2011

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, 5 | Description :The Recipient shall have paid/ secured funds for payment in an aggregateamount equal to FCF 12 billion in a seggregated account for compensation of Displaced Persons affected by Phase 4 Highway Work |Due Date :30-Apr-2011
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, 6 | Description :The Recipient shall have opened a fully operational Replacement Landfill| Due Date :15-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V.7 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the resettlement of Displaced Persons tothe Resettlement Site shall not occur under the Project before said Resettlement Site qualifies as a Functioning Resettlement site.| Due Date :15-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V.8 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that (i) the Mbeubeuss Landfill be closed tothe general public and cease to be receiving and openly burning waste " Non-Operational Status" . | Due Date :15-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V.8 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that (ii) the Mbeubeuss Landfill not reachsuch Non-Operational Status prior to the satisfaction of the requirements set forth in Section V.6 of Schedule 2 to this Agreementregarding the availability of a Replacement Landfill | Due Date :15-Dec-2013
